cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for group anomaly detection, which involves generating models to detect irregular group distributions. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the emphasis on image pixels in the paper, cs.CV is the most likely category, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CR.
